The Telegraph - Calcutta
 ICC to recruit umpires manager
London: In an effort to arrest the decline in umpiring standards, the ICC has decided to recruit an umpires high performance manager, who will work with its contracted officials. The chief responsibility of the person to be chosen for the new post would be to help develop all ICC-contracted umpires by introducing and monitoring training and development programmes, the games world governing body said in a statement on Friday. The development programmes should cover the areas of physical and mental conditioning, skill development, match preparation and match day activities.  (PTI)  Copyright 
